claim.claim-text:
A method for fabricating emulated wood with pores and fibers, comprising the steps of:
immersing a plurality of synthetic fibers (13) configured parallel in a plane into a resin (14) so that the resin (14) is coated on the surfaces of the plurality of synthetic fibers (13) and in the gaps (131) between the plurality of synthetic fibers (13);
placing the plurality of synthetic fibers (13) between two sheets (11, 12) so that the plurality of synthetic fibers (13) and the two sheets (11, 12) are attached to each other, wherein the two sheets (11, 12) are planar sheets (11, 12) made from a uniform composition comprising a thermoplastic elastomer, a foaming agent and a crosslinking agent;
carrying out a heat-press process on outer surfaces of the two sheets (11, 12) so that the foaming agent in the two sheets (11, 12) undergoes microcellular foaming after being heated and forms dense closed pores (B) in the two sheets (11, 12), and so that the composition on inner surfaces of the two sheets (11, 12) expands towards the plurality of synthetic fibers (13) and penetrates through the gaps (131) between the plurality of synthetic fibers (13) to be intertwined by pressure from microcellular foaming of itself and surroundings; and
cooling the two sheets (11, 12) to yield an emulated wood board (10),
wherein the inner surfaces of the two sheets (11, 12) after microcellular foaming form irregular contact surfaces with the plurality of synthetic fibers (13) and are densely and firmly combined in one by adherence force of the resin (14).

An emulated wood with pores and fibers, comprising:
a plurality of synthetic fibers (13), configured parallel in a plane;
a resin (14), coated on the surfaces of the plurality of synthetic fibers (13) and in the gaps (131) between the plurality of synthetic fibers (13); and two sheets (11, 12), which are planar sheets (11, 12) made from a uniform composition comprising a thermoplastic elastomer, a foaming agent and a crosslinking agent, and are attached to two corresponding sides of the plurality of synthetic fibers (13), wherein after a heat-press process is carried out on the two sheets (11, 12), the foaming agent in the two sheets (11, 12) undergoes microcellular foaming and forms dense closed pores (B) in the two sheets (11, 12) so that the composition on inner surfaces of the two sheets (11, 12) expands towards the plurality of synthetic fibers (13) and penetrates through the gaps (131) between the plurality of synthetic fibers (13) to be intertwined by pressure from microcellular foaming of itself and surroundings, and wherein the inner surfaces of the two sheets (11, 12) form irregular contact surfaces with the plurality of synthetic fibers (13) and are densely and firmly combined in one by adherence force of the resin (14) to yield the emulated wood.
